Some of this stuff controlled by GIT
------------------------------------

$ apt-get install git-core

$ cd ~/work
$ git init
$ git add stanford/ algorithms/ fossilix/ os/

$ git config --global user.name "Your Name Comes Here"
$ git config --global user.email you@yourdomain.example.com

$ git config --global color.diff auto
$ git config --global color.status auto
$ git config --global color.branch auto

$ git commit

------------------------------------
To clone this repository:

$ git clone git@github.com:0xfe/experiments.git

Then, work on your local changes, commit, and push.

You can also pull occasionally with:

$ git pull

Note: Never pull when you have uncommited changes. Bad Bad.

------------------------------------
Repository administration:

To bring the local working directory in sync with HEAD:

$ git reset --hard HEAD

-------------------------------------

Ignore list in .gitignore (in project root). Contents:

# Lines starting with '#' are considered comments.
# Ignore any file named foo.txt.
foo.txt
# Ignore (generated) html files,
*.html
# except foo.html which is maintained by hand.
!foo.html
# Ignore objects and archives.
*.[oa]
ruby_sess.*
.*.swp
.hi
*.pyc

------------------------------------

Workflow:

$ git branch newthingaby

$ git branch
  newthingaby
* master

$ git checkout newthingaby
... do stuff ...

$ git commit -a

$ git checkout master

$ git merge newthingaby

(If conflicts, fix them, then submit.)

$ git branch -d newthingaby

$ git push
